Defendant Calvin Markus Clayton in court with Attorney Richard E. Poulson.  Defendant Calvin Markus Clayton in custody.  
Karl Peter Hayes appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: dds.  


Matter before the Court for Sentencing.  Hearing proceeded.  Parties in receipt of PSI; no corrections to report.  Statements made by state, Bethann B., defense, and defendant. 
 
COUNT 2:  The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 10 YEARS, CONCURRENT to time being served with credit for 9 days. 

The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 5 YEARS.  

The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 5 YEARS.

The defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program ONLY AFTER SERVING 1 YEAR OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT ON THIS SENTENCE:

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
*Obtain AODA assessment and complete follow-up care/treatment;
*Absolute sobriety- submit to random urine screens;
*Participate in Cognitive behavioral therapy program;
*Participate in Vocational rehabilitation training/schooling;
*Participate in Parenting class;
*Obtain GED or HSED;
*Provide DNA sample- pay surcharge;
*Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, fees, assessments, and costs;

The Court recommends that the defendant participate in Former's Anonymous Program (optional).  The Court orders restitution in the stipulated amount of $2,000 payable to Crime Victim- joint and several with Kelsea Smith (15CF000648).  The Court ordered all financial obligations and restitution (PAID FIRST) to be paid through collection of sums by the Department of Corrections from 25% of prison funds and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment.

Defendant is informed he may not possess and/or own any firearms or body armor.
Defendant is informed he may not vote in any election until his civil rights have been reinstated.  
Defendant is informed of his right to appeal this sentence. 
